Additionally, the use of a model to investigate this phenomenon suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also deals with the exchange and aggregation of information, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on the behavior of individuals in a network suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) sub-category. The cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category is also a possibility, given the paper's use of a model to investigate a real-world phenomenon.
